<main class="portfoliopages">

	<h3>Portfolio - David Povey Photography</h3>
    
    <div class="wrapper">
    	<div id="dpbanner">
    	<img class="responsive" src="assets/images/dpmac.png" alt="David Povey photography">
    	</div><!--end dpbanner-->
        
        <div class="brieftext">
        <h4>The Brief</h4>
        <p>This was my first web design project and the brief was to create a brand new photography site which showcased as much of my clients photography work as possible.</p>
        <br>
        <div class="line"></div>
        <br>
        <h4>The Process</h4>
        <p>I started by drawing out wireframes to map out what each page should look like.  The original idea was to have a collage of pictures on the home page which would act as links to the different categories.  However, the client wanted something more traditional and elegant looking and he was able to produce photoshop designs of exactly what he wanted which I then translated that into HTML and CSS.</p>
        <br>
        <div class="line"></div>
        <br>
        <h4>The Outcome</h4>
        <p>The finished web site looks elegant and clean.  It isn't responsive but as no website is ever really finished, we are hoping to redesign it later this year in order to bring it up to date.</p>
        </div><!--end brieftext-->
        <div class="portfolioimages">
        <div class="left">
        <img class="responsive" src="assets/images/dpportpage1.png" alt="david povey photography">
        <p>The weddings page like most of this sites pages relies heavily on positioning to create the structure of text and images.</p>
        </div><!--end left-->
        <div class="right">
        <img class="responsive" src="assets/images/dpportpage2.png" alt="david povey photography">
        <p>The portraits page shows clear images to highlight the different styles of portraits that the photographer has.</p>
        </div><!--end right-->
        </div><!--end portfolioimages-->
